Class Request

java.lang.Object
model.Message
model.Request
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable
Direct Known Subclasses:
BadRequest
public class Request
extends Message
The request object sent by client containing information specified in the outline. Request's attributes are mutable in order for it to be built from an object stream.

    • getEncoded

      public byte[] getEncoded()
      Encode request object to bytes for transmission. The encoding is as follows: |0 |1 |2 |3 - x-1 |x |x+2 - y-1|y | +--+----+--+--------+--+---------+--+ |0 |type|0 |filename|0 |mode |0 | +--+----+--+--------+--+---------+--+

      type is if the request is read(2) or write(1). filename is a UTF-8 encoded string. mode is a UTF-8 encoded string.

      x is the separator between the filename and the mode and is not at a fixed position within the encoding. y is the termination byte and can be at any point before the maxMessageSize.

      Returns:
      The byte encoded request object.
